# .dockerignore — CodeKrack API
#
# Controls two different things, and the second one is the important one:
#   1. what `fly deploy` uploads to the remote builder
#   2. what actually ends up INSIDE the image, via `COPY backend/ ./`
#
# The build context is the REPO ROOT (fly.toml -> build.dockerfile =
# backend/Dockerfile), so every path below is relative to the repo root, not to
# backend/.
#
# These patterns are deliberately conservative. Nothing here relies on `!`
# re-inclusion, and no pattern can accidentally match backend/package.json or
# backend/package-lock.json, which the deps stage needs. Small root config files
# (vite.config.js, index.html, fly.toml...) are left in the context on purpose —
# they total a few KB, and excluding them would risk breaking the build to save
# nothing.

# ---- Secrets ----------------------------------------------------------------
# THIS IS THE PART THAT IS NOT OPTIONAL.
#
# `COPY backend/ ./` copies dotfiles. Without the line below, backend/.env is
# baked into an image layer: SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (bypasses RLS on every
# table), DATABASE_URL, EMAIL_PASS, GH_API_TOKEN. Layers are permanent and
# readable by anyone who can pull the image; deleting the file in a later layer
# does not remove it from the earlier one.
#
# It would also break the deploy *silently*. server.js calls dotenv.config(), and
# dotenv does not override real env vars — so Fly secrets still win where they are
# set. The danger is the ones you FORGET to set: backend/.env carries
# FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173, which SATISFIES the production boot guard at
# server.js:42 instead of tripping it.
#
# Verified locally (NODE_ENV=production, no FRONTEND_URL in env, .env present):
#   Server running on port 5099                                    <- guard passed
#   https://codekrack.vercel.app  -> no Access-Control-Allow-Origin <- site blocked
#   http://localhost:5173         -> Access-Control-Allow-Origin: http://localhost:5173
# The API boots clean, logs nothing wrong, refuses your own frontend, and mails
# students invite links pointing at localhost.
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/serviceAccountKey.json
**/*.pem
**/*.key
backend/RENDER_ENV_VARS.txt

# ---- node_modules -----------------------------------------------------------
# ~315MB of pointless upload, but the real damage is ordering. In the Dockerfile,
# `COPY backend/ ./` runs AFTER `COPY --from=deps /app/node_modules ./node_modules`,
# and Docker MERGES directories rather than replacing them. So the host tree (503
# packages — jest, eslint, nodemon, husky, supertest...) would overlay the clean
# `npm ci --omit=dev` tree (153 packages) and make --omit=dev decorative. Host
# modules are also resolved for this machine, not for node:20-alpine.
**/node_modules

# ---- Frontend — Vercel builds this; the API image never serves it ------------
src
public
dist
dist-ssr

# ---- Generated / dev-only ---------------------------------------------------
# docs/ is gitignored, but `fly deploy` uploads the local directory, not a git
# checkout — so gitignored files are still in the context unless named here.
docs
backend/tests
backend/logs
**/*.log
.git
.github
.vscode
.idea
